edu.harvard.cs262.DistributedGame

Interface GameSnapshot

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public interface GameSnapshot
extends java.io.Serializable
    The GameSnapshot interface represents the current snapshot of the game, which clients can render to display and view the current progression of the game. A GameSnapshot only contains as much information as clients need to render the game. It does not include hidden information used by servers.
    Version:
    1.0, April 2014
    Author:
    Twitch Plays Battleship Group
